parameters:
\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>No, no! Please let me go! Anything but forced dispatch,
please...!
\nc<Saki>Eh?! Se-senpai. What's that? What's going on?

\nc<Senpai>Oh, it's nothing serious. Employees who can't meet their
quarterly quotas are forcibly dispatched.
\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Please! I'll do it properly...! Just not forced dispatch...!

\nc<Senpai>Not that it's a death sentence or anything. Look, over
there. You can see the performance chart, right?
\nc<Senpai>That girl at the very bottom of the chart is the one.

\nc<Senpai>If you can't meet the quota assigned every quarter, you'll
be sent on forced dispatch too. But you should have some
leeway at first.
\nc<Saki>(Maybe I chose the wrong company... Should I run away now?)
\nc<Senpai>If you do as I say, there's nothing to worry about.

\bustMsgExp[1, 4]\nc<Saki>Yes, senpai... (It's true that Meary-senpai's performance is
at the top.)

\bustMsgExp[2, 2]\nc<Senpai>Well then, shall we start working overtime from today to
meet our quota?

\bustMsgExp[1, 1]\nc<Saki>(Eh? Could that be the secret to reaching the
top...?)\bustMsgExp[1, 0]I've finished the promotional work,
but... are there other tasks that require overtime?

\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Of course. There's plenty of work to be done, so don't
worry.
\bustMsgExp[1, 2]\nc<Saki>(Ugh, it's not great to run away on the first day either...)
\nc<>In the end, I ended up working crazy overtime with senpai...
